top.value: The objective of this project is to strengthen the ecosystem of early stage agricultural enterprises and agricultural innovation, through the provision of critical financing and technical assistance in financial management. The project is focused on agricultural SMEs which are underserved by the banking sector and too large for traditional microfinance organizations.

The general objectives of the fund are to: i) help the development and institutionalization of VC investing in Brazil through a North-South partnership that adds value by transferring global best practices; and ii) contribute to the growth of the life sciences industry in Brazil. The specific objectives of the fund are to: i) provide financing to innovative entrepreneurs and SMEs in Brazil; ii) create quality employment for local populations; and iii) improve SMEs corporate governance, auditing, management and intellectual property practices.
Increase youth employability through the strengthening of support systems for youth (capacity building and job insertion services)

The objective of the project is to strengthen the institutional capacity of Factoraje Pentagono in order to expand its factoring services to new clients. Factoraje Pentagono is one of the main actors in the factoring market in El Salvador and is the only one specialized and dedicated solely to this specific financing service.

The project aims to contribute to solving identified problems through improved technical and financial resources of the COP to address the unmet demand for financial products for housing for low-income population in Haiti.

The project seeks to support the creation of a seed fund, which will provide seed equity financing to a group of 12-16 emerging firms in the states of Santa Catarina and Parana, Brazil. The fund will target emerging firms with high growth potential in the energy, life sciences and information technology sectors. The investment in this fund is part of the strategy devised by the MIF and FINEP in their INOVAR II TA project that seeks to support the development of angel and seed investing.

El objetivo de este proyecto es fortalecer el ecosistema de las empresas agrcolas en etapa inicial y la innovacin agrcola, a travs de la provisin de financiamiento crtico y asistencia tcnica en la gestin financiera. El proyecto se enfoca en las PYMES agrcolas que son desatendidas por el sector bancario y demasiado grandes para las organizaciones microfinancieras tradicionales.

El proyecto pretende contribuir a la solucin de los problemas identificados a travs de mejorar los recursos tcnicos y financieros de las CP, para atender la demanda no atendida de productos financieros para la vivienda de la poblacin de bajos ingresos en Hait.

El FOMIN apoyar el crecimiento y consolidacin de un modelo de procesamiento agro-industrial eco-eficiente de frutas tropicales para la produccin de productos orgnicos especializados que incorpora a la red de proveedores de BASA a alrededor de 1,250 pequeos productores (450 actuales y 800 nuevos). Un modelo que representa una opcin sostenible de mercado (ingresos), mejora de productividad y mayor capacidad y resiliencia para los pequeos productores.

El fin del proyecto es contribuir a la creacin sostenible de empleo, el incremento de ingresos y mejores resultados sociales en Centroamrica y algunos otros pases, mediante el financiamiento y apoyo a empresas sociales que ofrecen soluciones a retos sociales y ambientales de la region.
